<div id="review_3419217020" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3419217020" />
    <a title="Evgeny" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9340136-evgeny"><img alt="Evgeny" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1544797852p2/9340136.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3419217020?book_show_action=true">Jul 08, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Evgeny" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Evgeny" href="/user/show/9340136-evgeny">Evgeny</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9340136-evgeny?shelf=hercule-poirot">hercule-poirot</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9340136-evgeny?shelf=crime-and-mystery">crime-and-mystery</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3419217020" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5147563739893688237"><i>&quot;May your mustaches never grow less.&quot;</i><br/><br/>I am not sure if everybody knows about this form of part entertainment. You fill a big container with water, drop some apples in there and make children get them out using only heir teeth. <br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1594260313i/29783549._SX540_.jpg' alt='apple bobbing' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/>This is called apple bobbing. Mrs. Oliver attended such a party (on Halloween). They ended up with a girl drowned in the same tab with apples. Mrs. Oliver recalled that same girl was boasting she had witnessed a murder one time. When you have this girl murdered just a coupl</span>
  <span id="freeText5147563739893688237" style="display:none"><i>"May your mustaches never grow less."</i><br><br>I am not sure if everybody knows about this form of part entertainment. You fill a big container with water, drop some apples in there and make children get them out using only heir teeth. <br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1594260313i/29783549._SX540_.jpg" alt="apple bobbing" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>This is called apple bobbing. Mrs. Oliver attended such a party (on Halloween). They ended up with a girl drowned in the same tab with apples. Mrs. Oliver recalled that same girl was boasting she had witnessed a murder one time. When you have this girl murdered just a couple of hours later, it makes one think. Mrs. Oliver did so and went to consult Hercule Poirot who started his investigation being intrigued by the situation. As a result he solved the mystery when the police had no clue. <br><br>In the reviews of later Poirot books I complained at least one of the two of the main necessary requirements for a good mystery was missing. What constitute a good mystery? A good mysterious (sorry for a bad unintended pun) crime and an investigator who is also an interesting character. Consider Hercule Poirot himself, Sherlock Holmes, Miss Marple, Nero Wolfe, (and to a lesser extend) Perry Mason, Lord Peter Wimsey, and even C. Auguste Dupin. <br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1594260420i/29783554._SX540_.jpg" alt="C. Auguste Dupin" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>They are all great colorful characters. <br><br>Now consider last Poirot books. Third Girl: Poirot was there, but the mystery did not appear until the last 10 pages or so. The Clocks: a good mystery, but Poirot bothered to appear long enough to just explain everything that was going on. I was ready to proclaim Evil under the Sun to be the last great Poirot novel when suddenly Dame Agatha seems to recall how to recreate the magic of her early Poirot books. Everything what made great Poirot novels such was there.<br><br>Grumpy old me <br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1594260514i/29783555._SX540_.jpg" alt="Grumpy" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>still has some complaints and nitpicking that prevented this book from getting anywhere close to 5 star rating. Agatha Christie got carried away with describing a park. Its description went on and on and on... I remember in one of his books Charles Dickens described a whole city in such a way I felt like looking at it. He used just one page for this. <br><br>Mrs. Oliver used to be a colorful character. Here she is so flat by the end I was getting annoyed with her. Finally anybody with even half of the brain functioning can solve the mystery by the middle of the book. It was interesting, but not very exciting to follow Poirot's fairly useless interviews after this. Do you want a sure way to solve later mysteries of Agatha Christie? Here goes: <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Are you sure?<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Ask yourself: who is getting (or who got) big money? This is the culprit even if he/she has an ironclad alibi <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>. Simple as this. Perfectly applicable in this case.<br><br>So in conclusion this was a very good book, but not satisfying enough read for 5 stars. At least it reminded why Poirot mysteries used to be great. <br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1594260571i/29783556._SX540_.jpg" alt="Reminder" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></["br"]></span>
  <a data-text-id="5147563739893688237" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


