<span id="freeTextContainer15805105719951055359">I&apos;ve been wanting to read this book for ages, just for the title alone. Luckily, it lived up to its name, featuring a Halloween party, with all kinds of themed games, and of course, murder. And who doesn&apos;t love a book that features Ariadne Oliver? I just adore her, and I wish Christie would have either written more books with her included, or featured some with her alone. She&apos;s just a peach!<br/>This book had a lot of atmosphere, and some philosophical musings on beauty, both in people and nature, as</span>
  <span id="freeText15805105719951055359" style="display:none">I've been wanting to read this book for ages, just for the title alone. Luckily, it lived up to its name, featuring a Halloween party, with all kinds of themed games, and of course, murder. And who doesn't love a book that features Ariadne Oliver? I just adore her, and I wish Christie would have either written more books with her included, or featured some with her alone. She's just a peach!<br />This book had a lot of atmosphere, and some philosophical musings on beauty, both in people and nature, as well as the role of reform versus punishment in criminal justice. A quite interesting book that has enough meat to ponder over long after you've read it. </span>
